    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Lift Set",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "G000319",
          "label": "Lift Set",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Rear differential fluid removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "621_3.0_jpn_11581945_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "With the vehicle horizontal, remove the filler bolt (A) and sealing washer (B). Remove the drain bolt (C) and sealing washer (D), and drain the dirty oil."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Rear differential fluid refill"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "621_3.0_jpn_11581946_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install a new sealing washer (A) and tighten the drain bolt (B). Inject the specified \"Honda Genuine Ultra HGO-μ (hypoid gear oil)\" through the filler bolt (C) hole to the same level as the underside of the screw. Specified oil Genuine Honda Ultra HGO-μ (hypoid gear oil) During overhaul 0.35L At exchange: 1 0.34L Install a new sealing washer (D) and tighten the filler bolt."
    }
  ],
